</section>

<!-- ═══ NARRATIVE ═══ -->
<section class="sp-narrative">
  <div class="sp-narrative-inner">
    <h2 class="sp-narrative-heading reveal">THE WORK</h2>

    <div class="reveal">
      <p>ADIB is the Middle East's leading Islamic bank — 1.5 million customers, 80% digital adoption, Euromoney's Best Islamic Bank 2025. I joined as Lead Product Designer to work on their most strategic digital initiatives.</p>

      <p><strong>Remit!</strong> was the flagship project — real-time cross-border transfers powered by Visa Direct, reaching 11 billion+ cards globally. I designed the end-to-end experience: recipient management, transfer flow, fee transparency, confirmation states, and error handling for a product that had to work across dozens of corridors with different regulatory requirements.</p>

      <p>I also designed the <strong>open banking UI/UX</strong> for the UAE's emerging Open Finance ecosystem — account aggregation, consent management, and third-party data sharing flows that had to balance regulatory compliance with genuine usability. And I led a <strong>design system overhaul</strong>, taking a chaotic collection of inconsistent components and restructuring it into an atomic system that the team could actually maintain.</p>

      <p>The tenure was short — six months — and the environment was slow and political. But the impact was recognized. I shipped meaningful work in a fraction of the time most enterprise designers get to warm up.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ TESTIMONIALS — Horizontal carousel ═══ -->
<section class="sp-testi">
